        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Teratorhabditis synpapillata Sudhaus, 1985 (light microscopy). (a) Neck (arrow pointing to the excretory pore); (b, c) anterior end at stoma and cuticle levels (arrow pointing to the amphid); (d) entire male; (e) entire female; (f) uterine egg; (g) female posterior end; (h) male posterior end. GP = genital papilla; ph = phasmid." ;
